    "stac_version": "1.1.0",
    "description": "This data set, part of the NASA Making Earth System Data Records for Use in Research Environments (MEaSUREs) program, consists of 6-day and 12-day 50 m resolution image mosaics of the Greenland coastline and ice sheet periphery. The mosaics are derived from C-band Synthetic Aperture Radar (C-SAR) acquired by the Copernicus Sentinel-1A and -1B imaging satellites starting in January 2015. \n\nSee <a href=\"http://nsidc.org/data/measures/gimp\">Greenland Ice Mapping Project (GIMP)</a> for related data.",
